    {
        "content": "<p>Does anyone know a reference for the fact that the <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Cauchy+complete+category\">Cauchy completion</a> of a category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathsf\">C</span></span></span></span> enriched over vector spaces is formed by taking the full subcategory of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{Vect}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Vect</span></span></span></span></span>-valued presheaves on  <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathsf\">C</span></span></span></span> consisting of retracts of finite coproducts of representables?</p>",
        "id": 368042836,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1687291592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If worst comes to worst, I'll settle for a reference for the analogous fact with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{Vect}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Vect</span></span></span></span></span> replaced by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{Ab}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Ab</span></span></span></span></span>.   Even the oldest sources I've looked at seem to take this for granted.</p>",
        "id": 368043075,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1687291667
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As far as I know (and you probably know this too), this notion of Cauchy completion for enriched categories was first defined by Lawvere in his 1973 paper \"Metric spaces, generalized logic, and closed categories\", where he claims that \"it can be shown\" that the characterization you mention holds for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{Ab}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Ab</span></span></span></span></span>, making it the bad sort of <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/folklore\">[[folklore]]</a>.  It seems like someone in the intervening 50 years ought to have written out a proof, but I don't know of one.</p>\n<p>The closest I can find right now is in <a href=\"http://www.tac.mta.ca/tac/volumes/37/28/37-28abs.html\">Cauchy completeness for DG-categories</a> by NikoliÄ‡, Street, and Tendas (2021), they show (Prop 6.1) that the Cauchy completion of a category enriched over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Z}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span></span></span></span>-graded abelian groups is formed by taking the full subcategory of enriched presheaves (\"right modules\") consisting of retracts of finite coproducts of <em>suspensions of</em> representables.  Inspecting the proof, it's clear that the grading could be by any abelian group instead of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Z}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span></span></span></span>, and taking it to be the trivial group yields the result for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{Ab}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Ab</span></span></span></span></span>.  But surely there must be an earlier and better reference than that.</p>",
        "id": 368070935,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1687302745
    }
]